
[1]conservation

   CONSERVATION, n. [L. See Conserve.] The act of preserving, guarding or
   protecting; preservation from loss, decay, injury, or violation; the
   keeping of a thing in a safe or entire state; as the conservation of
   bodies from perishing; the conservation of the peace of society; the
   conservation of privileges.
